text: Jacqueline Laudré (married name Jacqueline Mulot, 2 August 1910 — 9 April 2007) was a French track and field athlete specialized in the 80 metres hurdles, high jump and long jump events. Laudré represented France at international tournaments, including at the 1930 Women's World Games and the Olympics of Grace in 1931. In the 80 metres hurdles event at the 1930 Women's World Games she finished third in the heats but was eliminated in the semi- finals. The next year she was also eliminated in the semi-finals in the 80 metres hurdles event at the Olympics of Grace. At the national championships she became French national champion in the 80 meter hurdles in 1932, 1933, 1934 and 1943; in the high jump in 1930, 1933 and 1934; and in the long jump in 1932 and 1934.Docathlé2003, Fédération française d'athlétisme, p. 414 In 1933, she set a new French high jump record with 1.52 metres. She was the younger sister of Lucienne Laudré-Viel, who also became multiple times French national champion in the high jump and long jump. ==References== Category:1911 births Category:2007 deaths Category:French hurdlers Category:High jumpers Category:French long jumpers Category:People from Saint-Cloud Category:Sportspeople from Hauts-de-Seine
